  "prompt": "What is the procedure to apply to an RTI?",
  "response": "Here's the step-by-step procedure to apply for an RTI (Right to Information) in India:\n\n1. Identify the Public Information Officer (PIO)\n- Find the correct government department or office\n- Locate their designated PIO\n\n2. Prepare the RTI Application\n- Write in simple, clear language\n- Specify the information you want\n- Include your name and contact details\n- Be precise and specific about the information\n\n3. Application Submission\n- Use the standard RTI application form\n- Submit in person or by post\n- Can be handwritten or typed\n- Pay the prescribed application fee\n- Fee can be paid through:\n  - Demand draft\n  - Postal order\n  - Cash\n  - Indian Postal Order\n\n4. Application Requirements\n- Provide your full name and address\n- Attach required identification proof\n- State information sought clearly\n- Specify preferred language/mode of receipt\n\n5. Follow-up\n- Keep application receipt\n- Note down registration number\n- Track application status\n- Expect response within 30 days\n\n6. Appeals\n- If request is rejected, can file first appeal\n- Then second appeal to Information Commission\n\nNote: Each state might have slight variations in the exact procedure.",
